@node What "What is it?!?"

        @{b}So, what is it?@{ub}

At first, it is @{b}@{u}NOT@{ub}@{uu} an amiga program!!!

Some may remember the little proggy ECH0, a PeeCee proggy that
showed a random anti-pc tagline.

But... it has two limitations:
        - It doesn't draw much attention
        - It was written in Pascal @{"(structured programming sucks!)" link Pank}

So, here I come with an alternative:
        - It makes the PeeCee beep
        - It uses large letters
        - It waits until a key is pressed
        - It's written in assembly (int*l assembly SUCKS!)

Well, copy it to the DOS directory on @{b}any PeeCee you can get your hands on@{ub},
make it hidden (ATTRIB +H HIT.EXE)
and add the line 'HIT' to the AUTOEXEC.BAT!!!

And... @{u}Hit any PC user to continue@{uu}
@endnode
@node Why "How could I go that low"

Now you might be wondering why I went that low by coding in int*l assembly?!?

Well, sometime you'll have to... Like a part of the study I guess...
After doing the same semester for the 2˝th time it is about time to swallow
your pride and start doing things. Even if it means that you'll have to
code some boring little I/O proggy's in assembly on those lame PeeCees...

So there...
@endnode
